                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a radio-television address to the American people, made in Washington on the
                    evening of February 29 following his return from Lisbon, Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName> reviewed in some detail
                    the discussions and decisions reached by the North Atlantic Council during its
                    meetings in Lisbon. For the text of the address, see Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 10, 1952, page 363.</p>
                <p>For Secretary <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName>’s brief
                    personal account of the Lisbon meetings sent to President Truman in messages of
                    February 24 and 26, see <hi rend="italic">infra</hi> and <ref target="#pg_175"
                        >page 175</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
